name: e-commerce-app
description: A microservice-based e-commerce application built with Java, Spring Boot, and SQL, handling customer management, orders, payments, notifications, and product information.

name: JobApp_SpringBoot
description: This repository contains two different architectures of the JobApp project:  JobApp Monolith: A single-application architecture. JobApp Microservices: A modularized architecture built with a microservices approach. Both submodules are separate Git repositories included as submodules in this main repository.

name: Domic-UserService
description: A large project based on the architecture of distributed systems, each of its microservices uses ( Clean Architecture ) and takes advantage of many application patterns of software engineering

name: cbd-3354-assignment-01-c0918066-frontend
description: This is a React application that serves as the user interface for the Microservices Backend. It allows users to upload files, manage user accounts, and view user information seamlessly.

name: social-media-app
description: This is a full-stack MERN (MongoDB, Express, React, Node.js) application designed as a modern social media platform. It incorporates robust architecture and cutting-edge technologies to ensure scalability, performance, and maintainability.

name: EmployeeManagementSystem
description: Created using a contemporary tech stack (technology base) that is composed of HTML, CSS, Javascript, React Applications for Frontend, Spring Boot/Microservices designed for Backend along with SQL as the Database Search Engine.

name: AD_User_Manager_REST_API
description: A Spring Boot-based microservice for managing Active Directory users and groups via RESTful APIs. Supports user creation, update, deletion, enable/disable, group retrieval, and adding/removing users from groups. Simplifies Active Directory integration for enterprise applications.

name: Hotel-Rating-System
description: The Hotel Rating System is a microservices-based application designed to allow users to rate and review hotels. It provides features for managing users, hotels, and their ratings, ensuring a seamless and scalable experience for both users and administrators.

name: ROADmates
description: ROADmates is a carpooling application leveraging microservices architecture with Spring Boot, Angular, MongoDB, PostgreSQL, Kafka, and Zipkin. It features API Gateway, Keycloak for authentication, Eureka for service discovery, and Docker for containerization, ensuring scalability, security, and real-time communication

name: spring-framework6-with-springboot3
description: Master Spring Framework 6 and Spring Boot with hands-on projects! This repo covers Spring Core, MVC, AOP, Security, Microservices, and tools like Docker & Maven. Ideal for Java developers at all levels looking to build high-performing, scalable, and secure enterprise applications.
